 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-036 DETAIL: TASK DECAY MECHANISM. Tasks untouched for 5+ sessions should auto-decay to P4 priority. Implementation: (1) Add :task/last-session-touched (Instant, One) attribute to schema. (2) On any task interaction (show, go, close, update), record current session timestamp. (3) In methodology_gaps() or harvest, scan for tasks where last-session-touched is >5 sessions stale AND priority < P4. (4) Auto-downgrade to P4 with a retraction+assertion of :task/priority. (5) Report in braid status: 'N tasks auto-decayed to backlog'. This is a self-cleaning mechanism — the task system should converge toward only active work being visible. SPEC: No existing spec element. Need new INV-TASK-NNN for task lifecycle management. ACCEPTANCE: After 5 sessions without touching task X, X.priority == P4. Task decay count appears in status. Manual priority override persists (decay only applies if no explicit interaction)."
